						"title": "Forrester: The State of Zero Trust Edge",
						"subtitle": "Speed up your network modernization journey without the tradeoffs",
						"copy": "Organizations often have to juggle performance, resilience, and security when it comes to running their infrastructure. Networks are constantly under attack from sophisticated cyber threats. Global infrastructure suffers from slow, unreliable connections, and managing complex network environments has become a nightmarish and expensive operational burden. Traditional network solutions leave organizations vulnerable to devastating DDoS attacks, performance bottlenecks, and escalating security risks that can cripple digital operations. \n\nThis report provides an in-depth analysis of the evolving landscape of Zero Trust security architectures, emphasizing their critical role in safeguarding modern enterprises.\n\nKey insights from the report include:\n- Zero Trust as a strategic imperative\n- Challenges organizations face in integrating these models with existing infrastructure and workflows\n- Technologies and vendors in the Zero Trust space\n- Regulatory and compliance considerations\n",
